label.value: increased number of nuclear foci

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of nuclear foci are increased.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to kinetochore during mitotic M phase

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is abnormal during mitotic M-phase.

label.value: decreased protein localization to kinetochore during mitotic prometaphase

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is decreased during prometaphase of mitosis.

label.value: abolished protein localization to kinetochore during mitotic prometaphase

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome does not occur during prometaphase of mitosis.

label.value: sensitivite to trolox

definition.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to trolox. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of trolox that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abolished nuclear foci

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nuclear foci are absent.

label.value: normal actin cable morphology during mitotic interphase

definition.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, and structure of actin cables are normal during mitotic interphase (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased nuclear pore complex clustering

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the nuclear pore complexes are more clustered together than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K5 acetylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 5 of histone H4 at the silent mating type cassette occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K8 acetylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 8 of histone H4 in silent mating-type cassettes occurs to a higher extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K16 acetylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 in silent mating-type cassettes occurs to a higher extent than normal.

label.value: normal oxygen consumption

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of oxygen consumed by cells in a given time is normal.

label.value: increased centromeric inner repeat transcript level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNAs transcribed from the centromere inner repeat region are present at greater levels than normal.

This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere inner repeat region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere inner repeat sequences. For levels of RNA transcribed from an exogenous reporter gene placed in the inner repeat region, consider 'decreased chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat region' (FYPO:0003412).

label.value: normal centromeric RNA level during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNAs transcribed from the centromere measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere t region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of endogenous RNAs.

label.value: normal centromeric inner repeat transcript level

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNAs transcribed from the centromere inner repeat region are present at normal levels (i.e. indistinguishable from wild-type).

This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere inner  repeat region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere inner repeat sequences.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K20 monomethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is decreased.

label.value: decreased RNA polymerase II CTD binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which binding by a gene product to the RNA polymerase II CTD domain is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased RNA polymerase II CTD Ser5-P binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which binding by a gene product to the RNA polymerase II CTD domain phosphorylated serine 5 is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased Spt5-CTD binding

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which binding by a gene product to the Spt5 CTD domain is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased histone H3-S10 phosphorylation during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone H3-S10 phosphorylation is decreased.

label.value: decreased protein localization to processome

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the processome is decreased.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in the centromere central core occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at the centromere central core is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished histone H4 binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H4 binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere central core during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in the centromere central core is abolished.

label.value: equational sister chromatid segregation during achiasmatic meiosis I

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which sister kinetochores become separated during the first meiotic nuclear division, and sister chromatids subsequently separate to result in equational segregation, only visible in the absence of chiasmata. Equational sister chromatid separation is caused by bi-orientated attachment of sister chromatids.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at centromere central core during meiotic prophase I

definition.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the centromere central core is increased during the meiotic prophase I.

label.value: normal replication fork arrest

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at a natural  replication barrier is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during meiotic prophase I

definition.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is increased during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: normal protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during meiotic prophase I

definition.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is normal during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: sensitive to trolox

definition.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to Trolox (antioxidant). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of Trolox that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9Me binding

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H3-KMe binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9Me binding

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H3-KMe binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is increased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased reticulophagy during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which autophagic degradation of the endoplasmic reticulum occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased protein localization to plasma membrane during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane is decreased.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at the centromere outer repeat is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 methylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal at the centromere inner repeat.

label.value: normal meiotic cell cycle entry

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell enters the meiotic cell cycle normally: i.e after conjugation with cellular fusion and karyogamy with nuclear fusion.

label.value: equational sister chromatid separation at meiosis I

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic sister chromatid separation occurs in meiosis I due to erroneous merotelic kinetochore attachment.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at the centromere inner repeat region is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: delayed orthogonal actomyosin contractile ring assembly from randomly oriented actomyosin filaments

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell exhibits randomly misoriented actin and myosin II filaments, eventually forming a regular orthogonal actomyosin contractile ring. Although the onset of filaments assembly is not delayed, the cell takes more time complete the formation of an orthogonal actomyosin contractile ring.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleus during hypoxia

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is increased during hypoxic stress.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during hypoxia

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished during hypoxic stress.

label.value: normal microfilament motor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate or other property of a microfilament motor activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein neddylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the neddylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abolished.

label.value: normal histone H3-K14 acetylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 is normal at the  silent mating-type cassette (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished chromatin binding at promoter region

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) at one or more promoter regions does not occur.

label.value: decreased antisense RNA level during heat stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of antisense RNA measured in a cell is lower than normal duing heat stress. Antisense RNA is transcribed from the coding, rather than the template, strand of DNA.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 methylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in silent mating-type cassettes does not occur.
